HEADWORD: Liliidae
<hw>Liliidae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>one of four subclasses or
superorders of Monocotyledones; it comprises 17 families including:
<fam>Liliaceae</fam>; <fam>Alliaceae</fam>; <fam>Amaryllidaceae</fam>;
<fam>Iridaceae</fam>; <fam>Orchidaceae</fam>;
<fam>Trilliaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> subclass <subclass>Liliidae</subclass>.</syn>⟦br⟧
